## Selection rationale
- Phase 0 research: GZ has 20 Sudoku variants but ZERO multi-grid overlapping type
- Samurai Sudoku is the highest-SEO Sudoku variant on the open web
  (samurai-sudoku.com, freesamuraisudoku.com 1001+ puzzles, samuraisudoku.org
  with 12+ overlapping variants: Twodoku, Triple Doku, Butterfly, Windmill, Cross, Sohei, W, Flower)
- Rules: 5 standard 9x9 grids in quincunx/cross; each grid's standard Sudoku
  rules apply; corner 3x3 boxes are shared between adjacent grids
- Generator: build 1 center grid + 4 corner grids each constrained so its
  bottom-right/bottom-left/top-right/top-left 3x3 box matches the center's
  corresponding corner box. Keep shared cells as givens to make uniqueness
  check per-grid tractable.

